            Julie Dahlof Kramme
          
          
            
              I research school and community-based interventions
              that support people with intellectual and developmental
              disabilities to participate in communities of their
              choice. My research line focuses on self-determination and
              interventions that support adolescents with disabilities
              to learn to read.
              I am a Researcher at the Institute on Community
              Integration and a PhD student in Educational Psychology at
              the University of Minnesota. I love bikepacking and
              planning the next trip.
